reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 26, 2022
reviews.reviewText: This is a double stroller for their baby dolls that's just like a real twin or double stroller. It has real features like a storage basket, seat belts, and even a shade canopy. This is made with high quality fabric that doesn't easily rip or tear and trust me my niece tried because she sits in this and tries to get pushed. This is made with EVA foam wheels for extra smoothness while pushing the babies around. The stroller is lightweight and easy for them to push or carry around. It's easy to fold and store to take with you. It has a foam grip handle and a basket underneath for all the doll accessories. It fits dolls up to 15"

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Our daughters have been testing this pushchair for a couple of weeks and they're happy with it. Assembly was easy enough and it does look nice, but looking at the finished assembled product is massively underwhelming when you consider the cost of it.I ordered this and put it together to show my other half before telling her the price. She had no complaints and found no massive flaws or imperfections, and then I told her the price tag! This is pushchair is a decent enough toy but is something you'd expect to pay £10-£15 for, maybe £20 at a push. At £49.99 you're getting close to the toy versions of well-known prams and pushchairs and this doesn't compare.Overall, we'd give the product a thumbs up for quality but there is nothing to justify the inflated price.
